articles.title: HS Prannoy wins Malaysia Masters, beating China's Weng Hong Yang in men's singles final | Mint - Mint
articles.description: HS Prannoy showed great composure and resolve during a 94-minute battle to notch a 21-19 13-21 21-18 victory against China's world number 34 Weng Hong Yang, a 2022 Asian Championships bronze medallist.
articles.content: Star Indian shuttler HS Prannoy ended a six-year-long title drought with a three-game win over China's Weng Hong Yang in a pulsating men's singles finals at the Malaysia Masters Super 500 tournament … [+4284 chars]
